p://push.cx/2006/sociable-1-2\";s:8:\"comments\";s:41:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-1-2#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sun, 26 Mar 2006 07:49:52 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Peter Harkins\";}s:8:\"category\";s:12:\"codesociable\";s:4:\"guid\";s:32:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-1-2\";s:11:\"description\";s:249:\"<p>\r\nI\'ve just fixed a few more WordPress 1.5 bugs to create <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable 1.2</a>. There are also some css changes so that weird themes do fewer weird things to the display of Sociable (and man, do they do a lot).\r\n</p>\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";s:466:\"<!-- Sociable:Update date=\"2006-03-26\" -->\r\n<p>\r\nI&#8217;ve just fixed a few more WordPress 1.5 bugs to create <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable 1.2</a>. There are also some css changes so that weird themes do fewer weird things to the display of Sociable (and man, do they do that a lot).\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThis release of Sociable owes a lot of thanks to <a href=\"http://www.ajaydsouza.com/\">Ajay D&#8217;Souza</a> for working with me to debug Sociable.\r\n</p>\";}s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:38:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-1-2/feed/\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:249:\"<p>\r\nI\'ve just fixed a few more WordPress 1.5 bugs to create <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable 1.2</a>. There are also some css changes so that weird themes do fewer weird things to the display of Sociable (and man, do they do a lot).\r\n</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:466:\"<!-- Sociable:Update date=\"2006-03-26\" -->\r\n<p>\r\nI&#8217;ve just fixed a few more WordPress 1.5 bugs to create <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable 1.2</a>. There are also some css changes so that weird themes do fewer weird things to the display of Sociable (and man, do they do that a lot).\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThis release of Sociable owes a lot of thanks to <a href=\"http://www.ajaydsouza.com/\">Ajay D&#8217;Souza</a> for working with me to debug Sociable.\r\n</p>\";}i:6;a:12:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Sociable 1.1\";s:4:\"link\";s:32:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-1-1\";s:8:\"comments\";s:41:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-1-1#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Sun, 26 Mar 2006 02:29:32 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Peter Harkins\";}s:8:\"category\";s:12:\"codesociable\";s:4:\"guid\";s:32:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-1-1\";s:11:\"description\";s:66:\"<p>\r\nI\'m pleased to announce Sociable 1.1, a bugfix release.\r\n</p>\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";s:1231:\"<!-- Sociable:Update date=\"2006-03-25\" -->\r\n<p>\r\nI&#8217;m pleased to announce <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable 1.1</a>, a small bugfix release.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 150%\">\r\nIf you find any bugs, please <a href=\"mailto:ph@malaprop.org\">mail me</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThis release fixes two bugs that occurred when running WordPress 1.5 or PHP 5. Also, Sociable now checks to make sure that it was uploaded correctly (and provides instructions on how to fix the upload), so if you had problems with images not appearing or appearing as a vertical list, this should help you out. There&#8217;s also a minor performance improvement thanks to <a href=\"http://chait.net\">David Chait</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLastly, <a href=\"http://solo-technology.com\">Chris Kasten</a> added <a href=\"http://co.mments.com\">co.mments.com</a> to the list of supported sites.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLook for Sociable 2.0 in two or three weeks to support Spanish and German. If you&#8217;d like to help out and now a langauge I&#8217;d like to hear from you. I&#8217;ll also like to add more sites from the list on the <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable homepage</a>, so watch this blog for detailed instructions on how to help in a few days.\r\n</p>\";}s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:38:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-1-1/feed/\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:66:\"<p>\r\nI\'m pleased to announce Sociable 1.1, a bugfix release.\r\n</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:1231:\"<!-- Sociable:Update date=\"2006-03-25\" -->\r\n<p>\r\nI&#8217;m pleased to announce <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable 1.1</a>, a small bugfix release.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 150%\">\r\nIf you find any bugs, please <a href=\"mailto:ph@malaprop.org\">mail me</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThis release fixes two bugs that occurred when running WordPress 1.5 or PHP 5. Also, Sociable now checks to make sure that it was uploaded correctly (and provides instructions on how to fix the upload), so if you had problems with images not appearing or appearing as a vertical list, this should help you out. There&#8217;s also a minor performance improvement thanks to <a href=\"http://chait.net\">David Chait</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLastly, <a href=\"http://solo-technology.com\">Chris Kasten</a> added <a href=\"http://co.mments.com\">co.mments.com</a> to the list of supported sites.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nLook for Sociable 2.0 in two or three weeks to support Spanish and German. If you&#8217;d like to help out and now a langauge I&#8217;d like to hear from you. I&#8217;ll also like to add more sites from the list on the <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable homepage</a>, so watch this blog for detailed instructions on how to help in a few days.\r\n</p>\";}i:7;a:12:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"Sociable 1.0\";s:4:\"link\";s:31:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-10\";s:8:\"comments\";s:40:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-10#comments\";s:7:\"pubdate\";s:31:\"Fri, 17 Mar 2006 03:15:00 +0000\";s:2:\"dc\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";s:13:\"Peter Harkins\";}s:8:\"category\";s:15:\"codewebsociable\";s:4:\"guid\";s:31:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-10\";s:11:\"description\";s:251:\"<p>\r\nI\'ve been quiet the last week because my free time has been taken up by finishing <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable</a>, a plugin to the WordPress blog software. It\'s the reason there are the cute little icons down below this post.\r\n</p>\";s:7:\"content\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";s:976:\"<!-- Sociable:Update date=\"2006-03-16\" -->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nI&#8217;ve been quiet the last week because my free time has been taken up by finishing <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable</a>, a plugin to the WordPress blog software. It&#8217;s the reason there are those cute little icons down below this post.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 150%\">\r\nIf you find any bugs, please <a href=\"mailto:ph@malaprop.org\">mail me</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere&#8217;s not much for me to add to the description I put on its homepage, so let me take a moment to say how nice it is to develop a WordPress plugin. The WP folks clearly took time to make things as easy as possible. It&#8217;s easy for PHP to devolve into terrible messes of spaghetti code, but WP&#8217;s system of hooks, filters, and options presents a welcoming niche to the aspiring plugin author. Thanks, guys!\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nI&#8217;ve enjoyed developing Sociable so much, I&#8217;m wondering what plugin to write next&#8230;\r\n</p>\";}s:3:\"wfw\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentrss\";s:37:\"http://push.cx/2006/sociable-10/feed/\";}s:7:\"summary\";s:251:\"<p>\r\nI\'ve been quiet the last week because my free time has been taken up by finishing <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable</a>, a plugin to the WordPress blog software. It\'s the reason there are the cute little icons down below this post.\r\n</p>\";s:12:\"atom_content\";s:976:\"<!-- Sociable:Update date=\"2006-03-16\" -->\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nI&#8217;ve been quiet the last week because my free time has been taken up by finishing <a href=\"http://push.cx/sociable\">Sociable</a>, a plugin to the WordPress blog software. It&#8217;s the reason there are those cute little icons down below this post.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 150%\">\r\nIf you find any bugs, please <a href=\"mailto:ph@malaprop.org\">mail me</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nThere&#8217;s not much for me to add to the description I put on its 